THE ONLY LOSER
HERE IS TYRESE.

00:24:58.230 --> 00:25:02.330
BUT CAN HE NEGOTIATE
IN OTHER SITUATIONS?

00:25:02.330 --> 00:25:04.800
WE ASKED OUR PARENTS TO
DELIBERATELY KNOCK OVER THESE

00:25:04.800 --> 00:25:11.370
MARBLES AND THEN TO ASK THEIR
CHILDREN NOT TO TELL ON THEM.

00:25:11.370 --> 00:25:18.730
DON'T TELL THEM
IT WAS MOMMY OKAY?

00:25:18.730 --> 00:25:21.300
LYING ON BEHALF OF OTHER
PEOPLE IS A STAGE OF MORAL

00:25:21.300 --> 00:25:25.500
DEVELOPMENT NOT USUALLY
REACHED UNTIL EIGHT OR NINE.

00:25:25.500 --> 00:25:30.000
NOT SURPRISINGLY, MOST OF OUR
CHILDREN WERE NOT THERE YET.

00:25:30.000 --> 00:25:34.530
MOM!!

00:25:34.530 --> 00:25:36.630
THEY WERE SO EAGER TO
TELL ON THEIR PARENTS,

00:25:36.630 --> 00:25:39.170
THAT THEY CAME
LOOKING FOR US.

00:25:39.170 --> 00:25:41.030
COME HERE.

00:25:41.030 --> 00:25:44.070
&nbsp DADDY DROPPED
&nbsp THE MARBLES!

00:25:44.070 --> 00:25:47.000
BUT HOW WOULD
TYRESE GET ON?

00:25:47.000 --> 00:25:50.500
&nbspWHO WAS IT?

00:25:50.500 --> 00:25:52.930
&nbspHOW COME THEY'RE ON
&nbspTHE FLOOR?

00:25:52.930 --> 00:25:55.570
THE CONFLICT BETWEEN BEING
TOUGH MINDED, WITHOUT HAVING

00:25:55.570 --> 00:26:00.500
THE SKILLS TO CARRY IT
OFF, LEAVES HIM SILENT.

00:26:00.500 --> 00:26:09.630
&nbspWAS IT MOMMY
&nbspTYRESE?

00:26:09.630 --> 00:26:13.230
&nbspWELL THERE ARE TWO
&nbspPEOPLE IN ONE ROOM...

00:26:13.230 --> 00:26:24.370
&nbspDID YOU TOUCH
&nbspTHEM?

00:26:24.370 --> 00:26:27.030
BUT THERE WAS ONE CHILD THAT
SIMPLY DIDN'T TELL ON HIS MOM

00:26:27.030 --> 00:26:30.230
BUT SOLD HER
RIGHT DOWN THE RIVER.

00:26:30.230 --> 00:26:35.930
PLEASE DON'T TELL
ON MOMMY.

00:26:35.930 --> 00:26:39.370
DON'T TELL THEM!

00:26:39.370 --> 00:26:41.770
SO WHERE DID NATHAN LEARN
TO TAKE SO MUCH DELIGHT

00:26:41.770 --> 00:26:46.730
IN SHOPPING HIS MOM?

00:26:46.730 --> 00:26:48.170
HE'S LIVED ALL HIS LIFE HERE.

00:26:48.170 --> 00:26:50.470
IN THE SMALL MARKET
TOWN OF GALSTON,

00:26:50.470 --> 00:26:57.670
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE
AYRSHIRE HILLS.

00:26:57.670 --> 00:27:02.930
AT SCHOOL, NATHAN PRICE IS
A STICKLER FOR THE RULES.

00:27:02.930 --> 00:27:09.570
WE'RE ALLOWED TO RUN
BUT NOT IN THE CLASSROOM.

00:27:09.570 --> 00:27:13.030
WE RUN OUTSIDE.

00:27:13.030 --> 00:27:15.830
&nbspWHY DO YOU THINK
&nbspWE NEED RULES?

00:27:15.830 --> 00:27:19.930
&nbspNATHAN.

00:27:19.930 --> 00:27:21.900
SO WE KNOW
WHAT TO DO.

00:27:21.900 --> 00:27:24.130
&nbsp SO YOU KNOW EXACTLY
&nbsp WHAT TO DO.

00:27:24.130 --> 00:27:27.870
&nbsp THAT'S RIGHT.

00:27:27.870 --> 00:27:30.930
HE'S VERY AWARE
OF HELPING OTHERS.

00:27:30.930 --> 00:27:33.430
VERY AWARE YES HE'S
A VERY KIND CHILD.

00:27:33.430 --> 00:27:36.570
HE'S A VERY SETTLED CHILD.

00:27:36.570 --> 00:27:39.030
HE'S JUST A WEE BOY
THAT'S JUST A PLEASURE

00:27:39.030 --> 00:27:42.370
TO HAVE IN YOUR CLASS.

00:27:42.370 --> 00:27:44.900
BUT LIKE ALL CHILDREN HE
ALSO WANTS TO BE POPULAR

00:27:44.900 --> 00:27:46.570
WITH HIS SCHOOLMATES.

00:27:46.570 --> 00:27:50.530
AND HE DOES THAT IN A
VERY DIFFERENT WAY.

00:27:50.530 --> 00:28:00.530
HE'S GOOD AT DOING CROUCHING
AND JUMPING AND STUFF.

00:28:00.530 --> 00:28:02.900
HE'S DOING LOADS
OF FIGHTING.

00:28:02.900 --> 00:28:05.200
BUT NOT FOR LONG.

00:28:05.200 --> 00:28:08.500
AT HOME, THE RULES EVEN
HAVE MORE STRUCTURE

00:28:08.500 --> 00:28:16.800
EVEN IF THEY ARE A
LITTLE DIFFERENT.

00:28:16.800 --> 00:28:22.600
NATHAN IS ENCOURAGED TO
MEDITATE ON A REGULAR BASIS.

00:28:22.600 --> 00:28:24.730
HE WAS TAUGHT BY
HIS FATHER RICHARD.

00:28:24.730 --> 00:28:29.800
A BUDDHIST WHO
MEDITATES EVERY DAY.

00:28:29.800 --> 00:28:31.400
I WASN'T BORN A BUDDHIST.

00:28:31.400 --> 00:28:33.930
I ALWAYS HAD A PROBLEM
WITH THE RELIGIONS...

00:28:33.930 --> 00:28:35.470
THE STUFF THAT YOU
LEARNED AT SCHOOL,

00:28:35.470 --> 00:28:37.670
THE STUFF THAT YOU
LEARNED FROM YOUR FAMILY.

00:28:37.670 --> 00:28:40.600
THAT NEVER SAT WELL WITH ME.

00:28:40.600 --> 00:28:42.730
I THINK NATHAN IS THE TYPE
OF CHILD WHO BENEFITS

00:28:42.730 --> 00:28:46.970
WELL FROM STRUCTURE.

00:28:46.970 --> 00:28:51.070
HIS MOM RUTH IS
EQUALLY UNCONVENTIONAL.

00:28:51.070 --> 00:28:53.330
LETS SEE IF YOU CAN
HUG A TREE COME ON.

00:28:53.330 --> 00:28:56.170
HANDS AND STRETCH ME.

00:28:56.170 --> 00:28:57.630
I DON'T FIT IN.

00:28:57.630 --> 00:28:58.970
THAT'S VERY...

00:28:58.970 --> 00:29:00.600
NO, I DON'T FIT IN.

00:29:00.600 --> 00:29:03.300
I'M ONE OF THE MOMS THAT
DROPS THE KIDS OFF AT SCHOOL

00:29:03.300 --> 00:29:05.170
AND I SMILE AT PEOPLE
BUT I DON'T REALLY

00:29:05.170 --> 00:29:09.200
KNOW MANY PEOPLE
VERY WELL.

00:29:09.200 --> 00:29:15.930
THEY NEVER HAVE FITTED IN.

00:29:15.930 --> 00:29:19.630
WHEN THEY MOVED TO THE AYRSHIRE
COUNTRYSIDE TEN YEARS AGO,

00:29:19.630 --> 00:29:21.600
THEY WERE DETERMINED TO
BRING THEIR CHILDREN UP

00:29:21.600 --> 00:29:23.470
WITH THEIR OWN VALUES.

00:29:23.470 --> 00:29:26.900
UNCONTAMINATED BY
MAINSTREAM SOCIETY.

00:29:26.900 --> 00:29:28.600
IT'S AN IDEAL THERE
STILL TRYING TO PUT

00:29:28.600 --> 00:29:32.100
INTO PRACTICE TODAY.

00:29:32.100 --> 00:29:33.070
EVEN AT BEDTIME.

00:29:33.070 --> 00:29:35.300
THE STORK STUFFED HIMSELF
WITH ALL THE PEACHES

00:29:35.300 --> 00:29:36.470
HE COULD
POSSIBLY EAT.

00:29:36.470 --> 00:29:38.300
WOULD YOU HAVE
DONE THAT?

00:29:38.300 --> 00:29:39.400
I WOULD.

00:29:39.400 --> 00:29:40.970
YOU WOULD HAVE TAKEN
ALL THE PEACHES

00:29:40.970 --> 00:29:42.770
AND NOT LEFT ANY
FOR ANYONE ELSE?

00:29:42.770 --> 00:29:44.130
I WOULD TAKE SOME.

00:29:44.130 --> 00:29:45.770
YOU WOULD HAVE
TAKEN SOME.

00:29:45.770 --> 00:29:46.700
YES.

00:29:46.700 --> 00:29:51.370
WHAT DID THE BUDDHA
DO TO THE MONKEY?

00:29:51.370 --> 00:29:54.270
HE TOLD HIM
WHAT TO DO.

00:29:54.270 --> 00:29:56.370
THE RIGHT THING.

00:29:56.370 --> 00:30:00.170
WHAT IS THE MOST IMPORTANT
TEACHING OF THE BUDDHA?

00:30:00.170 --> 00:30:01.500
DO NO HARM.

00:30:01.500 --> 00:30:02.800
SAY IT AGAIN
NATHAN.

00:30:02.800 --> 00:30:04.970
DO NO HARM.

00:30:04.970 --> 00:30:13.630
COME THE WEEKEND,
NATHAN NEEDS TO GET OUT.

00:30:13.630 --> 00:30:17.000
AND NOTHING, NOT EVEN
THE POURING RAIN CAN STOP

00:30:17.000 --> 00:30:22.570
GALSTON'S KEENEST
BIRD WATCHER.

00:30:27.470 --> 00:30:34.200
I COME IN HERE AND REST.
STAY REALLY QUIET.

00:30:34.200 --> 00:30:36.370
SO TELL ME WHAT
BIRDS HAVE YOU SEEN?

00:30:36.370 --> 00:30:48.530
WOODPECKERS, WOOD-PIGEON
AND A GREEN FINCH.

00:30:48.530 --> 00:30:52.170
BUT THE BIRD BOX SERVES
ANOTHER PURPOSE AS WELL.

00:30:52.170 --> 00:30:57.300
NOT JUST LOOKING FOR BIRDS,
BUT ESCAPING FROM HUMANS.

00:30:57.300 --> 00:31:00.930
&nbspWHY DID YOU GO
&nbspIN THERE?

00:31:00.930 --> 00:31:05.000
&nbsp SO NOBODY CAN
&nbsp FIND ME.

00:31:05.000 --> 00:31:09.370
SOMETIMES THOUGH HE
JUST CAN'T GET AWAY.

00:31:09.370 --> 00:31:14.500
SOMETIMES HE'S NASTY WHEN
WE COME BACK AFTER SCHOOL

00:31:14.500 --> 00:31:19.030
AND SOMETIMES HE'S NASTY WHEN
WE'RE TAKING OUR FRIENDS HOME.

00:31:19.030 --> 00:31:23.500
AND THEN WE ALWAYS HAVE
A CARRY ON IN THE CAR.

00:31:23.500 --> 00:31:27.100
WELL HE HAVE IN
MY NOSE ONCE.

00:31:27.100 --> 00:31:27.970
&nbspWHY?

00:31:27.970 --> 00:31:29.270
OUCH!

00:31:29.270 --> 00:31:31.000
BECAUSE WE WERE
FIGHTING TOGETHER.

00:31:31.000 --> 00:31:33.530
OUCH!

00:31:33.530 --> 00:31:36.370
AND THEN MEDITATION
SERVES ANOTHER PURPOSE.

00:31:36.370 --> 00:31:40.370
&nbsp WHY DO YOU HAVE THIS
&nbsp SHRINE IN YOUR BEDROOM?

00:31:40.370 --> 00:31:47.570
BECAUSE IF I'VE BEEN BAD I
HAVE TO THINK WHAT I'VE DONE.

00:31:47.570 --> 00:31:53.700
&nbsp WHAT ARE YOU
&nbsp THINKING ABOUT?

00:31:53.700 --> 00:31:56.600
NEVER GET INTO TROUBLE.

00:31:56.600 --> 00:32:00.030
FOR ALL OF US, STRONG
VALUES AND ABSOLUTE RULES

00:32:00.030 --> 00:32:06.270
CAN BE VERY HARD
TO LIVE UP TO.

00:32:07.670 --> 00:32:11.870
IN BIRMINGHAM, TYRESES MOM'S
COMMITMENT TO HER PRINCIPLES

00:32:11.870 --> 00:32:15.030
MEANS THINGS ARE
CHANGING FOR THE FAMILY.

00:32:15.030 --> 00:32:18.230
MARIA'S CONCERNED THAT
LIKE MANY BLACK BOYS,

00:32:18.230 --> 00:32:20.930
TYRESE MAY NOT THRIVE
IN BRITAIN AND SO

00:32:20.930 --> 00:32:25.070
MISS OUT ON THE OPPORTUNITIES
OPEN TO HIS WHITE PEERS.

00:32:25.070 --> 00:32:27.930
SO SHE'S CONTEMPLATING
A BIG GAMBLE,

00:32:27.930 --> 00:32:32.670
IN THE GAMBIA.

00:32:40.930 --> 00:32:42.900
I HAVE A FIFTEEN YEAR PLAN,

00:32:42.900 --> 00:32:44.800
AND BY THE FIFTEEN
YEARS ARE UP

00:32:44.800 --> 00:32:47.930
I WILL HAVE THREE PROPERTIES
IN THREE COUNTRIES.

00:32:47.930 --> 00:32:51.500
SO GAMBIA IS THE FIRST,
THEN THE CARIBBEAN

00:32:51.500 --> 00:32:54.230
AND KEEP YOUR FINGERS
CROSSED, MAYBE AMERICA.

00:32:56.130 --> 00:32:59.870
IT'S NICE TO SEE THE BLACK
PEOPLE IN HIGH POSITIONS

00:32:59.870 --> 00:33:04.430
AND YOU GUYS ARE
THE MINORITY.

00:33:04.430 --> 00:33:06.970
MARIE HAS DECIDED TO
BUY SOME LAND HERE.

00:33:06.970 --> 00:33:08.800
BUT TO DO BUSINESS
IN THE GAMBIA,

00:33:08.800 --> 00:33:11.070
SHE IS FINDING YOU
HAVE TO DUCK AND DIVE

00:33:11.070 --> 00:33:14.600
JUST AS MUCH AS
IN BIRMINGHAM.

00:33:14.600 --> 00:33:19.170
THERE IS NO WAY I'M GONNA
BE SPENDING 16 AND 20 GRAND.

00:33:19.170 --> 00:33:20.400
I AIN'T GOT THAT
KIND OF MONEY.

00:33:20.400 --> 00:33:22.100
THEY LOOK AT WHAT YOU'RE
PAYING IN ENGLAND

00:33:22.100 --> 00:33:23.570
AND THEY'RE SAYING THEY
WANT THE SAME HERE.

00:33:23.570 --> 00:33:25.200
IT DOESN'T WORK LIKE THAT.

00:33:25.200 --> 00:33:26.430
YOU HAVEN'T GOT
THE INFRASTRUCTURE.

00:33:26.430 --> 00:33:28.330
YOU HAVEN'T GOT RUNNING WATER,
YOU HAVEN'T GOT ELECTRICITY.

00:33:28.330 --> 00:33:30.130
AND YOU HAVEN'T GOT
TELEPHONE POINTS.

00:33:30.130 --> 00:33:31.370
YOU GOTTA LOOK AT THAT.

00:33:31.370 --> 00:33:34.400
IT'S NOT REALISTIC.

00:33:34.400 --> 00:33:38.300
WHILE SHE'S AWAY, TYRESE
AND HIS SISTER TANISHA

00:33:38.300 --> 00:33:41.330
ARE WITH THEIR
GRANDMOTHER BEVERLY.

00:33:41.330 --> 00:33:43.930
TELL ME WHAT ISN'T BORING?

00:33:43.930 --> 00:33:48.800
EVERYTHING IS BORING.

00:33:48.800 --> 00:33:51.030
BEVERLY LIVES
JUST DOWN THE ROAD.

00:33:51.030 --> 00:33:54.530
AND OVER THE YEARS HAS SPENT
A LOT OF TIME WITH TYRESE.

00:33:54.530 --> 00:33:57.170
HE'S GOT A VERY
STRONG CHARACTER HERE.

00:33:57.170 --> 00:33:59.600
HE'S GOT ACTUALLY
A NICE CHARACTER.

00:33:59.600 --> 00:34:01.500
ACTUALLY I LIKE TYRESE.

00:34:01.500 --> 00:34:05.200
HE HAS A TIME WHEN HE
DOESN'T LIKE PEOPLE.

00:34:05.200 --> 00:34:06.570
DOESN'T WANT TO TALK
TO ANYONE

00:34:06.570 --> 00:34:10.570
BUT I ALWAYS SEEM TO ABLE
TO SWITCH HIM AROUND.

00:34:10.570 --> 00:34:12.830
PEOPLE'S FIRST
IMPRESSION OF TYRESE

00:34:12.830 --> 00:34:16.170
IS THAT HE'S BOISTEROUS,
HE'S A BOY AND ALL THAT.

00:34:16.170 --> 00:34:19.170
BUT IT'S NOT LIKE THAT.

00:34:19.170 --> 00:34:23.430
I THINK A CHILD HAS A RIGHT TO
BE ANGRY OR EXPRESS HIMSELF

00:34:23.430 --> 00:34:25.370
IN A CERTAIN WAY.

00:34:25.370 --> 00:34:27.630
YOU KNOW I DO THINK
THE CHILD SHOULD,

00:34:27.630 --> 00:34:30.070
AND HE DID.

00:34:30.070 --> 00:34:32.230
IT MAY BE THIS INSIGHT
THAT SETS TYRESE

00:34:32.230 --> 00:34:36.970
AT EASE IN HER COMPANY AND
HELPS HIS STRENGTHS COME OUT.

00:34:36.970 --> 00:34:39.270
IF YOU GIVE HIM
PROJECTS TO DO

00:34:39.270 --> 00:34:41.200
HIS TAKES IT RIGHT
THROUGH TO THE END.

00:34:41.200 --> 00:34:43.170
HE'S VERY GOOD THAT WAY.

00:34:43.170 --> 00:34:47.300
SO HE'S PICKED UP
THAT VALUE FROM HIS MOM.

00:34:47.300 --> 00:34:49.970
SHE'S NEGOTIATED BUYING A
PLOT OF LAND WHICH SHE HOPES

00:34:49.970 --> 00:34:54.070
WILL BECOME THE FIRST OF THE
FAMILIES PROPERTY EMPIRE.

00:34:54.070 --> 00:34:55.130
YOU'VE GOT THE SUN.

00:34:55.130 --> 00:34:56.570
YOU'VE GOT
THE SEA.

00:34:56.570 --> 00:34:58.570
IT'S A MORE LEISURELY PACE.

00:34:58.570 --> 00:35:01.330
PEOPLE ARE STILL
MAKING A LIVING,

00:35:01.330 --> 00:35:04.830
BUT IT'S NOT THAT
CUT THROAT, FAST PACE.

00:35:04.830 --> 00:35:06.530
EVEN IF YOU LOOK
AT PEOPLE WALKING,

00:35:06.530 --> 00:35:08.700
IT'S A LEISURELY STROLL.

00:35:08.700 --> 00:35:10.830
WHEN I SHOW THIS GAMBIAN
PERSON HOW WE WALK IN ENGLAND,

00:35:10.830 --> 00:35:13.830
SHE'S LIKE NO
AND I'M LIKE YAH.

00:35:13.830 --> 00:35:16.670
MARIE HOPES THAT THE GAMBIA
WILL BE A LITTLE MORE

00:35:16.670 --> 00:35:20.730
THAN JUST AN ENTREPRENEURIAL
OPPORTUNITY.

00:35:20.730 --> 00:35:22.370
I WANT MY CHILDREN
TO EXPERIENCE LIFE,

00:35:22.370 --> 00:35:23.970
NOT JUST ONE
PART OF THE WORLD.

00:35:23.970 --> 00:35:26.230
I WANT THEM TO KNOW DIFFERENT
ASPECTS OF THE WORLD..

00:35:26.230 --> 00:35:29.800
STIMULATE THEIR
IMAGINATION A BIT MORE.

00:35:29.800 --> 00:35:33.000
&nbspCOAT ON.

00:35:33.000 --> 00:35:34.270
NO!

00:35:34.270 --> 00:35:36.300
&nbspGET IT ON THEN.

00:35:36.300 --> 00:35:39.230
A FEW WEEKS LATER, THE
GAMBIA SEEMS A LONG WAY AWAY

00:35:39.230 --> 00:35:44.430
AS THE FAMILY HEADS INTO
BIRMINGHAM'S RUSH HOUR.

00:35:44.430 --> 00:35:46.970
BUT THE EXPERIENCE
HASN'T BEEN WASTED.

00:35:46.970 --> 00:35:48.970
GAMBIA'S BRING ME ON TO
SORT OF SAY THE THINGS

00:35:48.970 --> 00:35:50.730
THAT I WANT TO
ACHIEVE.

00:35:50.730 --> 00:35:53.000
THAT IF I WANT THE LIFE
THAT I WANT TO LIVE IN GAMBIA,

00:35:53.000 --> 00:35:55.700
I GOT TO DO
SOMETHING ABOUT IT,

00:35:55.700 --> 00:35:59.170
WHICH IS ONE OF THE REASONS
WHY I WANT TO OPEN UP A SHOP.

00:35:59.170 --> 00:36:01.130
MARIA'S FURTHERING
HER AMBITION

00:36:01.130 --> 00:36:03.370
TO MAKE LIFE BETTER
FOR HER FAMILY.

00:36:03.370 --> 00:36:10.470
BUT IS TYRESE DEVELOPING HIS
ABILITY TO GET WHAT HE WANTS?

00:36:10.470 --> 00:36:13.800
WE ASKED THE CHILDREN TO MOVE
THESE BALLS FROM ONE CONTAINER

00:36:13.800 --> 00:36:19.470
TO ANOTHER USING A
COMPLETELY UNSUITABLE SPOON.

00:36:24.400 --> 00:36:30.830
IT'S AN IMPOSSIBLE
TASK, SO WILL THEY CHEAT?

00:36:30.830 --> 00:36:35.570
IN SIMILAR EXPERIMENTS,
SCIENTIST ALL OVER THE WORLD

00:36:35.570 --> 00:36:37.970
HAVE OBSERVED THAT VIRTUALLY
ALL YOUNG CHILDREN

00:36:37.970 --> 00:36:39.470
WILL HAVE A GO.

00:36:39.470 --> 00:36:40.600
THEN,

00:36:40.600 --> 00:36:43.030
THEY WILL CHEAT.

00:36:43.030 --> 00:36:45.700
EVEN UNDER COMMUNISM.

00:36:45.700 --> 00:36:49.730
BUT WILL THEY ADMIT IT?

00:36:49.730 --> 00:36:52.930
THE RUSSIAN CHILDREN DIDN'T.

00:36:58.300 --> 00:37:03.200
ALL OUR CHILDREN
CHEATED TOO.

00:37:03.200 --> 00:37:04.900
THEY'RE LEARNING THAT
SOMETIMES YOU HAVE TO

00:37:04.900 --> 00:37:08.870
BEND THE RULES TO
GET THINGS DONE.

00:37:08.870 --> 00:37:11.700
BUT WOULD THEY ADMIT IT?

00:37:11.700 --> 00:37:13.270
&nbspDID YOU USE
&nbspYOUR HANDS?

00:37:13.270 --> 00:37:15.770
NO.

00:37:15.770 --> 00:37:17.600
HOW ABOUT TYRESE?

00:37:17.600 --> 00:37:19.170
&nbspDID YOU TOUCH THEM
&nbspWITH YOUR HANDS?

00:37:19.170 --> 00:37:20.600
YES.

00:37:20.600 --> 00:37:22.530
SOME.

00:37:22.530 --> 00:37:24.830
SOME WITH MY HANDS.

00:37:24.830 --> 00:37:27.770
THE ONES THAT FALLED OUT.

00:37:31.370 --> 00:37:35.230
COURAGEOUSLY, TYRESE WAS
ONE OF THE FEW WHO DIDN'T LIE.

00:37:35.230 --> 00:37:37.270
IT SEEMS HE'S FINDING
OUT THAT IT'S POSSIBLE

00:37:37.270 --> 00:37:39.570
TO ARGUE YOUR
CORNER.

00:37:39.570 --> 00:37:41.800
WHAT ABOUT EVE?

00:37:41.800 --> 00:37:43.270
&nbsp DID YOU USE
&nbsp YOUR HANDS?

00:37:43.270 --> 00:37:44.200
NO.

00:37:44.200 --> 00:37:45.930
NOT VERY MUCH.

00:37:45.930 --> 00:37:52.030
I DON'T THINK
I DID.

00:37:52.030 --> 00:37:54.870
SHE DOESN'T WANT TO LIE
BUT SHE ALSO DOESN'T WANT

00:37:54.870 --> 00:37:58.670
TO BE SEEN TO BE BREAKING
THE RULES.

00:37:58.670 --> 00:38:01.130
IT'S ONLY ONE OF THE MANY
DILEMMAS IN HER LIFE

00:38:01.130 --> 00:38:04.600
AT THE MOMENT.

00:38:04.600 --> 00:38:06.870
IT'S SPORTS DAY
REHEARSAL AT SCHOOL

00:38:06.870 --> 00:38:13.400
BUT EVE'S MIND IS ON HER
MOM AND THE UNBORN BABY.

00:38:13.400 --> 00:38:15.170
IT'S STRANGE REALLY.

00:38:15.170 --> 00:38:20.070
SHE WENT TO THE
HOSPITAL YESTERDAY.

00:38:20.070 --> 00:38:28.030
WELL, THERE'S JUST A
LITTLE SORT OF AN OPERATION.

00:38:28.030 --> 00:38:32.200
TIP THERE WINGS LIKE THAT...

00:38:32.200 --> 00:38:36.330
I WAS QUITE ILL, VERY SICK.

